📢🗣️Sharing this because the only way to stop behaviour like this is to speak up, speak out and share our stories. The ones acting in this manner need to feel embarrassed, not us!

👉🏼When we feel unsafe as women, we need to share. We need to teach our daughters not to stay silent in any situation that makes her feel unsafe and uncomfortable.
I will not be embarrassed because of the inappropriate actions of someone else towards me and I will not be afraid to share this story. Sadly, I know situations like this will never end but we do have a voice and we can use our voices, share our stories, say NO and stand up. 

I am using this situation as a teachable moment to NEVER stay silent even if it is a small encounter like this. Talk about it, call a friend, tell your parents, tell anyone you feel is safe, or use your platforms. When you feel unsafe as a woman you need to speak up and speak out😠😡 We need to teach our future generations this too.

#speakup #speakout #takeastand #womenspeakingout #womenrights #takingastand #takingaction
